metadata.name: LAND++ #11
metadata.description:
NOTE：
This work 《LAND++》 is a free mint work for collectors who own 《LAND》.
《LAND》 had a bug in it due to an error on my part, which caused the image to be blurred like an ink painting when displayed in Live View mode.
(This is a problem of misconfiguration of pixelDensity, and this problem can be avoided by setting the browser zoom size to 50% or less.)

This bug has been fixed in《LAND++》.
Thank you again to the collectors.

-----------------------------------------

It has been over a year since I released 《MOUNTAINS》 in 2023. In this work, while utilizing some of the same algorithms as 《MOUNTAINS》, we draw various landscapes with a simple code of less than 200 lines. By applying FLUX processing to geometric forms, we give a certain kind of gravity to the shapes.
Fertile lands, rugged terrains, desolate fields, and scorched earth（焼け野原） are generated.

1920×1080 px
p5js

metadata.name: hollow #192
metadata.description:
In 1993, Basque sculptor Eduardo Chillida proposed a project to create an immense void inside Tindaya, the Sacred Mountain of Fuerteventura's indigenous inhabitants. The hollow cube measuring approximately 45 x 50 x 65 meters was conceived as a space for "all the people" to "fully experience the tininess of humankind".

The idea of the project dates back to the 1980s, and it took the artist years of searching for the ideal mountain in different parts of the world. However, what was ideal for Chillida evoked a lot of controversy due to the environmental and social impact of the project. There was uncertainty about Tindaya's structural feasibility and the potential harm to the ancient petroglyphs engraved on its surface. What's more, the financial sustainability of the project's economic model would depend on hundreds of thousands of tourists visiting the site each year, converting a work of art into a holiday attraction.

Chillida called his project the Monument to Tolerance. Although it never came into existence, it has caused division and conflict since it was conceived.


"hollow" is an exploration of 256 voids in nonexistent natural monuments. Made of digital matter instead of stone and lacking cultural charge, its sole purpose is to contemplate the tininess of humankind.


-----

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the quality from preview to the resolution of a print of approximately 30cm in height. In live mode, click on PNG to save the rendered image.

Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes from a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones to render the image. 

Requirements: 1GB of RAM. The system needs up to 200 MB of free RAM for rendering square preview images and up to 400 MB of free RAM for rendering square images at the highest resolution. I tested on Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge / Windows, Mac OS, Android, and iPhone, but please make sure it works on your device before minting.

-----

Possible features:

color scheme: cairngorm, alborz, bardenas, atlas, bieszczady, watkins

proportions: square, wide, standard, narrow

frame: none, vignette, bright, dark, bright with vignette, dark with vignette

visitors: tourists, tourists and birds, solitary flock of birds, only light

metadata.name: Urban Flora #512
metadata.description:
Urban Flora is a generative artwork exploring interplay of natural and artificial forms created by Marcin Ignac / @marcinignac

http://marcinignac.com/projects/urban-flora/

The project was inspired by the 3/4/5G network infrastructure more and more present in the parks and greenery of our cities. Final Urban Flora transformed into a study of abandoned structures of a long forgotten civilisation.

The whole image is generative and/or procedural. Leaves are parametric, twigs and trees use the space colonisation algorithm, and the geometry is based on platonic solids transformed though series of operations.

Features determined at the time of minting:
- one of the platonic solids or a prism
- one of 15 geometry transformations
- a color theme
- leaves or detailed twigs
- leaf's spread and the amount of ridges

'g' / 'tree finger tap' - resolution and export
'drag' - rotate
'scroll' - zoom (on desktop)

Please note the project needs a decent GPU.

Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

--
With dedication to my wife.

metadata.name: Turbulence #52
metadata.description:
Swirly shapes are rendered by passes of poisson samples of a warped noise field. The noise shifts with each pass, creating a layered effect. 

Dense editions may take over 2 minutes to draw fully.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume at any time during the drawing.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a not 1:1 variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.

Common:
- 43 set palettes plus many more with combinations
- 3 color distribution methods
- 50/50 dark
- 50/50 monochrome with bright highlights 
- 3 drawing styles: lines, points, colored pencils
- 5 noises effects: full screen, distance from center, distance from bottom, horizontal center, vertical center, random circles, 3,5, or 7 horizontal and vertical bars
- Poisson point distribution based on set layers or the noise value

Rare
- 15% chance of a dark monochrome with gold strands

Copyright (c) 2022 Matt Perkins, hello@mattperkins.me, @nudoru on Twitter. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: Countdown #69
metadata.description:
80% of the benefits from primary sales will go to the nonprofit "One Earth", check out their mission and their projects in www.oneearth.org

---------------

We need your help! The Earth is melting!

"Countdown" is a project that tries to show some consequences of global warming and pollution. It does so by representing a glacier that will melt over time, acting as a Countdown for our time left to react to the Climate Crisis.

If you visit this token every other day, the melting will start to be noticeable, and around one year, most of the ice will be gone. The token will also show signs of pollution: the sky colors will desaturate, stars will be less visible on night palettes, and the ice and water will get dirtier. Lastly, the penguin families will start disappearing, as the ice melts and they lose their home.

All the information of the token is available on the browser's console (Features + Token evolution).

---------------
- 365 editions, as the ice will melt almost completely in one year
- 13 color palettes, with different rarities
- 3 ice shades
- Different number of penguin families
---------------

Press "s" to save a 2000x2000px png with the current state of the token

metadata.name: DeStijl Fortunes #132
metadata.description:
The best part of being full and happy and ready to leave the restaurant is opening the fortune cookie. Does it mean something? Does it have poor grammar and vague references? You know it's not really *for you* but it sure feels like it.
This collab between sgt_slaughtermelon and 0xphiiil creates simple pleasant DeStijl-influenced designs determined by your hash and inspired by Theo Van Doesburg that feature crypto-centric fortunes. Maybe they'll give you some *not financial advice* or maybe it will be a vague truism or an optimistic or pessimistic omen. Who knows? Part of the fun is imagining that it's for you and it's real - and if you don't like it, just open another cookie.

metadata.name: Vestige #70
metadata.description:
Vestige /ˈvɛstɪdʒ/: a trace or remnant of something that is disappearing or no longer exists.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Vestige is a GT that creates colorful gradients by layering thousands of transparent shapes. This can sometimes take a couple of seconds (depending on your machine).

Notes on Responsiveness:

When resizing the window, refresh the sketch and it will assume the new window dimensions. Zooming in and out will require you to also refresh the page.

Hit the N button and wait a short moment to explore a different [N]ew Vestige.
Hit the M button to return to the [M]ain seed, which represents your own original Vestige . Hitting the M button to update the GT after zooming does work, however you'll have to refresh to view at the new resolution.

- Best enjoyed in fullscreen.
